# Jarvis Investor Advisor

This project now includes a simple local Python chat interface for talking to an Azure AI agent.

## What you need

- Python 3.10+
- An Azure AI Foundry project endpoint
- An Azure agent name that already exists in your project
- Azure authentication available through Azure CLI or your developer identity

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

2. Copy the example environment file and fill in your values:
   ```bash
   copy .env.example .env
   ```

3. Edit .env and set:
   - AZURE_AI_PROJECT_ENDPOINT
   - AZURE_AI_AGENT_NAME
   - Optional: AZURE_AI_MODEL

## Run locally

```bash
python app.py
```

You will be prompted to enter messages. Type exit or quit to end the session.

## Notes

The app uses DefaultAzureCredential first, but if Azure CLI is not available it will fall back to a device-code sign-in in the terminal.
If you prefer the browser-based flow, set:

```env
AZURE_AUTH_MODE=interactive
```

If you want to use an API key stored in Azure Key Vault, set:

```env
AZURE_AUTH_MODE=apikey
AZURE_KEY_VAULT_URL=https://your-vault.vault.azure.net/
AZURE_API_KEY_SECRET_NAME=your-secret-name
```

If you are already using a service principal, you can also set:

```env
AZURE_TENANT_ID=...
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=...
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=...
```

## Verification

```bash
python -m unittest discover -s tests -v
```
